name: Doris
description:
Beads and fringe are all grown up in these soft, thick, warm scarves. Made of 100% brushed wool flannel, you'd think that they would be scratchy and unwearable next to the skin, but don't let that word "woool" fool you! These scarves are very soft and just slightly fuzzy, sewn of a double layer of fabric for extra warmth on the coldest days of winter and dressed up with irridescent beaded fringe for just a touch of classy style. 

They are generously sized with the camel colored scarves measuring approximately 60 inches x 12 inches, and the checked measuring 54 inches x 8 inches.



*Please note that due to the handmade nature of the materials and our items, some slight variations may exist.


Item #: SW01 and SW02

name: Beatrice
description:
If you crave light weight warmth and incredible softness, nothing can beat our limited edition Beatrice scarves!

Made of a 40/60 blend of Angora and Merino wool harvested from animals humanely and sustainably raised on a family farm in New England, the yarn for these scarves has been hand spun, giving it better structural integrity, which means that you can enjoy that characteristic Angora fuzziness without worrying about bits of bunny fur flying off and clinging to your eyelashes, lips, and everything else you come near.

After the yarn is spun, it is hand dyed in small batches, with the exception of the off white and light grey colors, which are not dyed at all but appear in the natural colors of the rabbits and sheep.

Each scarf has been hand knit in my original design and measures approximately 60 inches long by 6.5 inches wide. Every scarf comes with care instructions, a sample of textile soap with which to cleanse it, and a muslin drawstring bag for storage during the warmer months.



*Please note that due to the handmade nature of the materials and our items, some slight variations may exist.

name: Dhara
description:
In Hinduism, Dharā is one of the Vasus, gods of the physical cosmos. He represents the earth and the element earth, though Earth is usually the goddess Prithvi rather than a god. Dhārā is a Sanskrit term used to refer to the flow of a stream or waterfall.

I have named these scarves Dhara for their connection to the earth (made of cotton) and their flowing movement.

Just in time for the changing seasons, these beautiful scarves are made of 100% cotton hand woven in Java and fair trade imported. They are then hand dyed by me in a variety of saturated colors using low immersion, painting, and Japanese Shibori techniques.  These scarves are wonderfully soft and light weight enough to wear indoors or with a sweater on warmer days. The lovely drape of the cotton fabric makes them the perfect choice for dressing up a casual ensemble!


Each scarf measures approximately 72 inchees long x 14 inches wide with 2 inches of hand tied fringe at each end.

Colors: Coffee, Moss, Marmalade, Royal, Lime, and Cobalt (more colors and patterns coming soon!)
